import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of count over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    data['hour'] = data['time'].dt.hour
    avg_count_by_hour = data.groupby('hour')['count'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='hour', y='count', data=avg_count_by_hour)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average count by hour of the day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
